<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-20T06:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-20T06:44:00-05:00" n="518" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d518">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/565: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-20T11:00:00-00:44">May 20,
                                    1942—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 12:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>156. Department’s 113, May 16, 9 p.m. I have discussed with President
                            Barclay the question of Germans leaving Liberia and informed him of the
                            statement of the War Department in regard to the early arrival of
                            adequate forces which will enable him to submit the agreement to the
                            legislature.</p>
                        <p>President Barclay agrees with the suggestion concerning the Germans and
                            states that the German Consul General has already been informally
                            notified that if circumstances should change here the Germans would be
                            invited to leave the country. President Barclay now states that he will
                            immediately invite the Germans to leave Liberia.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>